  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Interior Designer",
  "description": "<p>The Interior Designer (Commercial) will be responsible for creating and delivering inspirational designs to meet the client's commercial needs. This is a full-time hybrid role located in Mandai with flexibility for some remote work. The Interior Designer (Commercial) will work closely with clients to ensure that the design and build process is completed according to their requirements while ensuring the work is completed on time and within budget.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work from rough sketches and specifications created by the project manager</li>\n  <li>Design plans using computer-aided design and drafting (CAD) software.</li>\n  <li>Draft and prepare layout drawings.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with designers, contractors and project managers on projects.</li>\n  <li>Revise drawings and layouts to accommodate changes and enhancements.</li>\n  <li>Knowledgeable to draw for C&amp;S, Mechanical and Electrical works using CAD</li>\n  <li>Manage project site vendors and progress</li>\n  <li>Ensure all works meet quality standards and government regulations</li>\n  <li>Ensure that the expenditure of the projects are kept within budget</li>\n  <li>Attend meetings and liaise with consultants, sub-contractors and any other parties involved in the project</li>\n  <li>Inspect off-site fabrication and on-site installation</li>\n  <li>Ensure that all the defects have been rectified before the arrangement for pre-site inspection</li>\n  <li>Perform any other ad hoc duties</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
